			Researchwork
			
			MAINACADEMICACHIEVEMENTS:
(1)CONSERVATIONBIOLOGY–Inrecentyears,conservationbiologystudieshavebeencarriedoutinseveralendangeredplantspeciesendemictoChina,suchasDysosmaversipellis,Dipteroniadyerana,Changiumsmyrnioides,andKirengeshomapalmata.Wehaveelucidatedtheunderlyingcausesofendangermentofthesespecies,anddevelopedconservationstrategiesforthem.Inaddition,asoftwarewasdeveloped(PGDC1.0)whichassistsinconstructingcorecollectionsofendangeredspeciesbasedontheiramong-populationallelefrequencydistributions.Theaboveresearchfindingshavebeenpublishedinavarietyofhighqualityinternationaljournals,includingAmericanJournalofBotany,ConservationGenetics,andPlantaMedica.Since2004,twoprizesforresearchachievementswereawardedtome:theSecondPrizeforScientificandTechnologicalAdvancementofZhejiangProvince(Dec.2008)andtheThirdPrizeforScientificandTechnologicalAdvancementofZhejiangProvince(Dec.2004).

(2)MOLECULARPHYLOGEOGRAPHYOFTEMPERATEPLANTENDEMICSINEASTASIA–BasedonourphylogeographicalstudiesofseveralEastAsianplantendemicsrestrictedtotemperate-deciduousforests,weconcludethat(i)componentsofthisforesttypeinSouthJapanandEastChinawereparticularlysensitivetorangefragmentation,isolation,andenhanced(incipient)speciesformationthroughouttheglacialandinterglacialperiodsofthe(Late)Quaternaryand(ii)thecurrentdistributionanddifferentiationofcomponentsofpresentlyisolatedwarmtemperate-deciduousforestsinEastChina,SouthJapanandSouthKorealikelyresultedfromacombinationofrelativelyancientvicariantandimmigrationevents(e.g.,fromSouthJapantoEastChina),atleastpre-datingthelastglacial/interglacialcycleofland-bridgeformationanddisruptionacrosstheEastChinaSea.

			
				
